# Rust (titular)

- **Toolchain**: Honor `rust-toolchain.toml`. The crate uses **edition 2021** (`Cargo.toml`).
- **Layout**: Library entry is `src/lib.rs`; the binary lives under `src/bin/titular/`. Follow existing module boundaries and naming.
- **Commands**: Prefer **`just`** over spelling out long `cargo` invocations. See `justfile` and root `AGENTS.md` for recipes (`build`, `build-full`, `lint`, `test`, `check`, `fmt`, etc.).
- **Before finishing a change**: Run `just check` (or at minimum `just fmt` + `just lint` + `just test` when behavior changes). Use `just lint-full` when edits touch features or `Cargo.toml` feature sets.
- **Features**: Default vs `minimal` / `full_application` / `display` matter for builds; use `just build-full` or `just build-min` when validating feature-specific code paths.
- **Style**: Match surrounding code. Prefer extending existing error handling and types over new parallel patterns. Do not add noise (redundant comments, drive-by refactors outside the task).
